      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. So if the interlacing points are maximized, it essentially limits the \"void space\" within the textile structure. If we were to increase the weft density significantly while keeping the warp density constant, how would that impact the dimensional stability and the overall barrier properties of the fabric? I want to ensure the weave is tight enough to be completely non-permeable to fine particulate matter.",
